According to the 2012-2016 American Community Survey, there are 155 housing units with a median housing value of $111,100 and a median housing income of $32,633. The male median income is $31,328 while the female median income is $25,694. Concurrently, 55.7% of the population lives in poverty, 75.1% have obtained a high school education, and 12.8% do not have health care. 1 military veteran resides within the community.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/search-results.html?page=1&stateGeo=none&searchtype=web&cssp=SERP&q=East+enterprise&search.x=0&search.y=0&search=submit|title=Search Results|publisher=United States Census Bureau|website=www.census.gov|language=en-US|access-date=2018-06-23}}</ref>

